ies for thinking, cognition and political action? The first analysis of the conceptual figures of queer-feminist thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFeminism. 0aGender identity. 0aQueer theory. 0aSex rolexResearch. 0aSexismxResearch. 0aWomen's studiesxResearch. 4aBiopolitik. 4aEpistemologie. 4aFeministische Philosophie. 4aGender. 4aIntersektionalität. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aOntologie. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aQueer Studies. 4aQueer Theory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh  aBiopolitics.  aCultural Studies.  aEpistemology.  aFeminist Philosophy.  aGender.  aIntersectionality.  aOntology.  aPostcolonialism.  aQueer Studies.  aQueer Theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839433492zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839433492423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839433492/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070101-2  PP Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DSWb2016  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016